<h2 id="mnist-with-bayesian-feed-forward-neural-networks">MNIST with Bayesian Feed-forward Neural Networks</h2>
<p><a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/bayesian-neural-network"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-View_on_GitHub-blue?logo=GitHub" alt="View on GitHub" /></a>
<a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/bayesian-neural-network/blob/main/BNN.ipynb"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Jupyter-Open_Notebook-blue?logo=Jupyter" alt="Open Notebook" /></a></p>

<div style="text-align: justify">I built a Bayesian Feed-forward Neural Network from scratch in PyMC3 and trained it on the MNIST handwritten digits data set. The model achieved an accuracy of 93.8% on the test set with a single hidden layer of \(N=128\) neurons.</div>
<p><br /></p>
<center><img src="assets/img/BNN_pred.svg" /></center>
<p><br /><br /></p>

<h2 id="modelling-the-impact-of-contact-tracing-apps-in-containing-the-covid-19-virus">Modelling the Impact of Contact-tracing Apps in Containing the COVID-19 Virus</h2>
<p><a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/covid-percolation"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-View_on_GitHub-blue?logo=GitHub" alt="View on GitHub" /></a>
<a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/covid-percolation/blob/master/Covid-Percolation.ipynb"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Jupyter-Open_Notebook-blue?logo=Jupyter" alt="Open Notebook" /></a>
<a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2004.07237.pdf"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/PDF-Read_Paper-blue?logo=adobe-acrobat-reader&amp;logoColor=white" alt="Read Paper" /></a></p>

<div style="text-align: justify">I investigate a percolation model for the ability of contact-tracing programmes to contain the COVID-19 virus proposed by Bulchandani et al. in a 2020 paper. Numerical results are discussed and related to the current epidemic situation.</div>
<p><br /></p>
<center><img src="assets/img/infection-graph-tracing.svg" /></center>
<p><br /><br /></p>

<h2 id="predicting-monthly-wildfires-in-the-us">Predicting monthly Wildfires in the US</h2>
<p><a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/us-wildfires"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-View_on_GitHub-blue?logo=GitHub" alt="View on GitHub" /></a>
<a href="https://github.com/christopheberle/us-wildfires/blob/main/us-wildfires.md"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/RMarkdown-Open_Notebook-blue?logo=R" alt="Open Notebook" /></a></p>

<div style="text-align: justify">In this notebook I am exploring hierarchical Bayesian models in PyMC3 in order to predict the number of wildfires in the US in the future. I will build a Log-Normal-Poisson model which accurately predicts the number of wildfires within a \(1\sigma\)-uncertainty.</div>
<p><br /></p>
<center><img src="assets/img/us-wildfires.png" /></center>

